# ISC Backend (Laravel)

## Naming (ISC 1.2)

- Variables: `camelCase` · private props: `_camelCase` (if used) · Classes/methods: `PascalCase` / `camelCase` per PSR
- Constants: `ALL_CAPS` · Interfaces: `I` prefix optional in PHP; prefer contracts in `app/Contracts`

## Style (ISC 1.3–1.4)

- No magic strings/numbers — config, enums, `config/*.php`
- Thin controllers → Form Request validation → Service/Action classes
- Public API methods: PHPDoc; explain WHY on non-obvious business logic
- No stray `dd()`, debug dumps, or unresolved TODO/FIXME

## Security (ISC 1.5)

- Validate at HTTP boundary (`FormRequest`); never trust client input
- Eloquent/query builder only — **no** raw SQL string concatenation
- Check **ownership/authorization** on every resource by ID (avoid IDOR)
- Mass assignment: `$fillable` / DTO whitelist — never `User::create($request->all())` with sensitive fields
- Secrets in `.env` only; never log email, phone, tokens, passwords, OTP
- Wrap unexpected errors; safe client messages; log internally with `trace_id`

## API (ISC 2.x–5.x)

- REST nouns, plural, lowercase: `GET /users`, max 3 path segments
- Business actions: `POST /users/{id}/reset-password`
- Standard JSON envelope: `success`, `data`, `error`, `meta` (with `request_id`, `trace_id`, `timestamp`)
- Business errors: HTTP 200 + `success: false`; technical errors: 4xx/5xx middleware
- Error codes: module prefix `AUTH_`, `USR_`, `ORD_`, `SYS_` — use enums/constants
- External HTTP/DB: timeouts from config; Laravel `Http::timeout()` + `CancellationToken` patterns where applicable

## Design (ISC 1.6)

- DI via constructor; no `new Service()` inside domain code
- Transactions for multi-step writes; avoid N+1 (`with()`, eager loads)
- Pagination on list endpoints; idempotency keys for create/payment-style POSTs where needed
- Rate limit auth/OTP routes

## Laravel specifics

- Policies/Gates for authorization; Spatie Permission when RBAC lands
- Use `API Resources` or dedicated response helpers for consistent envelope
- Queue long-running work; never block request on external AI/storage without timeout

